cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DB, cs.CR

This paper discusses the use of big data, mobile phone data, and social network analytics in credit scoring. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the ethical and regulatory implications of using such data. The paper also involves statistical and economic modeling, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DB (Databases). The use of credit information and financial inclusion also suggests cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as a possible category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of social network analytics, which falls under cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks).
